In this tutorial, I'll show you how to do a 4-hole Japanese binding. This is the basic traditional method of Japanese bookbinding (or stab binding).

Materials:
• 8.5 x 11 inch paper (about 30 pieces)
• Waxed thread

Tools:
• Pencil, cutting mat and ruler
• Needle and scissors
• Screw punch (learn more - http://bit.ly/VJAxK2) 
  or awl (see substitutes - http://bit.ly/Ylyz16)
• Binder clips (optional)

